dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit ran approximately every 2 weeks during CAPS/87 and CAPS/88. If Rs indicated in the unit DIDBREAK that they have broken up with a romantic partner previously asked about in ROMPART, the BREAKUP unit was administered. In it, Rs are asked how whether they lived with and/or were married to the partner. They then rate the breakup on a number of dimensions, and indicate the extent to which they felt each of eleven emotions about ending the relationship. They rate their current relationshi p with the x-partner, a number of factors contributing to the breakup, and indicate whether they are currently dating anyone else.

The unit was developed by Harry Reis, Bill Ickes, and Deborah Richardson.

No standard scoring.
